%p.mb-4
  Split, parse and clean human names into their component parts using GET or POST requests. Input from POST requests are limited to 500 lines. See the
  = link_to "Ruby gem", url("/developers/code")
  used in this service.

%dl
  %dt Base URL
  %dd.pl-2 https://api.bionomia.net/parse.json

  %dt ?names=
  %dd.pl-2 human name(s); use \r\n as line breaks, all content escaped for GET requests (required)

  %dt.mt-3 Example GET
  %dd.pl-2
    https://api.bionomia.net/parse.json?names=Henry+Robert+Nicollon+des+Abbayes%3B+Groom+Q%0D%0AMrs.+John+Errol+Chandos+Aberdeen

  %dt.mt-3 Example POST
  %dd
    %pre.pre-scrollable.bg-dark.text-white.border.rounded.p-3
      %code
        :preserve
          curl -X POST -d $'names=Henry Robert Nicollon des Abbayes; Groom Q\r\nMrs. John Errol Chandos Aberdeen' https://api.bionomia.net/parse.json

